headline: Starboard Value Builds Over 9% Stake in Engineering-Materials Maker Rogers
summary: Activist investor Starboard Value has a more than 9% stake in  Rogers Corp.  and plans to seek another round of changes at the engineering-materials maker to boost shares.  Starboard’s position in Rogers was disclosed Wednesday in a securities filing, confirming an earlier report from The Wall Street Journal.  Rogers, with a market value of around $1.3 billion, makes materials used in electric and hybrid cars, personal electronics and other industrial applications.
